## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Push notifications delivered via FCM for Android/Web Push and APNs for iOS when reminders are due, respecting user-chosen channels and quiet hours
- [ ] Email fallback reliably delivers reminders when push fails, with exponential backoff on repeated failures
- [ ] Server-side scheduler calculates nextTriggerAt accurately based on user timezone and habit schedule
- [ ] In-app Notifications Center displays all message types (reminders, challenge updates, friend invites, system messages) and supports read/unread state, filtering, and search
- [ ] Habit Detail page shows history, analytics, schedule, and per-habit reminders with real-time editing capabilities
- [ ] Settings & Preferences allow configuring channels, quiet hours, onboarding prompts, theme, and sync settings; changes persist and immediately affect delivery
- [ ] All API responses validated; data accessed with null-safe guards; arrays initialized as [] and objects with defaults
- [ ] UI adheres to the project’s design system, with accessible colors, typography, and responsive layout
- [ ] Comprehensive tests:
  - Unit tests for scheduling logic and reminder calculation
  - Integration tests for end-to-end delivery flow (mocked push/email)
  - UI tests for Notifications Center filtering/search and Habit Detail reminder editing

