## UI/UX Guidelines

Apply QuestHabit’s design system consistently across all components:

- Visual Style:
  - Color usage strictly follows the provided palette (orange #FF9A57 as primary, violet #7C61FF as secondary)
  - Soft peach-cream backgrounds with frosted-glass card aesthetics
  - Dark mode surfaces with near-black cards for emphasis
  - Subtle gradients (warm gradient #FF9A57 → #FFD7A8; purple gradient #7C61FF → #BFA7FF)
  - Elevations via soft shadows; minimal drop shadows for depth; glow used sparingly for celebratory states
- Typography:
  - Poppins/Inter-like rounded geometric sans
  - h1 700, h2 600, body 400, labels 500, numeric 700
  - Mobile typography targets: Title 20–24px, Subhead 16–18px, Body 14–15px, Caption 12px
- Layout:
  - Single-column vertical flow with stacked cards; bottom navigation with center FAB for new reminder
  - 8px grid multiples; 16–24px card padding; generous horizontal padding on mobile (16–20px)
- Components:
  - Cards: full-width with 16–24px corner radii; frosted glass effect on light surfaces
  - Buttons: primary pill with warm gradient; secondary outlined pills
  - Inputs: rounded rectangles with clear focus rings in purple
  - Charts: rounded bars with gradients; sparklines where space allows
  - Micro-interactions: subtle animations for hover/press; confetti for achievements
- Accessibility:
  - Sufficient color contrast; ARIA labels; keyboard accessible; option to adjust animation intensity if available

