## Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety

CRITICAL: Implement all code with runtime safety in mind.

- Supabase-like results handling:
  - const items = data ?? []
  - Guard arrays: Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- API responses:
  - const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- React state initialization:
  - useState<Type[]>([]) for arrays; useState<Type>({} as Type) for objects if needed
- Optional chaining and defaults:
  - const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}
  - Access nested properties safely: obj?.property?.nested
- Validation:
  - Validate inputs server-side and client-side
  - Validate time formats and timezone strings
- Null safety:
  - Never call .map/.filter/.reduce on undefined/null without guards

